Bafana Bafana are in camp ahead of the Afcon 2022 qualifers against Ghana and Sudan. South Africa are second in the group after winning three of their opening four qualifiers. The coach spoke to eNCA's Tshepo Thobane ahead of the fixtures. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Bafana Bafana are in camp ahead of the Afcon 2022 qualifiers against Ghana and Sudan. South Africa are second in the group after winning three of their opening four qualifiers. Molefi Ntseki and his charges can ill-afford a slip-up on the final two qualification hurdles. READ:Â Bafana Bafana beat Sao Tome amid TV blackout Ntseki's charges have been affected by COVID-19 regulations. Bongani Zungu, Dean Furman and Keagan Dolly won't be part of the squad. Their clubs have refused to release the players over fears they might contract the virus.